    <div class="thumb whole">
        <img src="/img/kimandremy.png" title="Kim Scott" alt="Kim Scott" />
        <div>
            <div>
               <h2> Kim Scott </h2>
			   <p> 	is a graduate student in the <a href=http://eccl.mit.edu/index.html>Early Childhood Cognition Lab</a> at MIT and Mama to three- ("AND A HALF!") -year-old Remy.  She developed Lookit in part because, as a single working parent, she wouldn't have been able to participate in research with her own son.</p>  
	<p><b>Research interests:</b> Origins of conscious experience, in particular how we put together information from both sides of the brain and how we learn about the structure of time
	<p><b>Hobbies:</b> Salsa dancing and bicycling
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

	<div class="thumb half" style='clear:left'>
